reviewText:
It's lovable Dick Van Dyke.  Anyone who misses pure mystery entertainment that leaves you relaxed, entertained and feeds your appetite for mysteries without blood and gore, this is for you.
Murder-She-Wrote fans, Father Dowling fans, Simon and Simon fans and Matlock fans really need to get the complete set of Diagnosis Murder series and have yourself a great feast for the kind of mysteries that make you feel good.
I love this show and am glad they've released more seasons. The picture quality was fine even though they give you a warning about using archived footage.

I have been waiting for the additional series of Diagnosis Murder to be issued.  As soon as I saw them at Amazon.com, I ordered them.  Now I'm waiting for the rest of the seasons so I have the complete set.  I enjoyed these when they were on TV, and now I can enjoy them on DVD.  Thank you

Just be aware if you are seeking the famous scene where Doctor Sloan (Dick Van Dyke) walks past a radio station studio and sees Rob Petrie (Dick Van Dyke) - the scene has been cut from this DVD. They didn't even include it as an extra. Unbelievable!!
love the guy and anything he does. diagnosis murder is clean, not too violent and dick always puts in just a bit of his humor to make me watch for it.
Diagnosis Murder is one of the many dvd sets I have that when there is nothing on tv (often), I can just throw one of these in and enjoy.
the review is the same as part one - GREAT!!  Timeless entertainment and quality acting for evening  entertainment are at its best.
Great deal, excellent whodunit, Dick Van dyke if one of the greatest entertainers of all time, must watch if you want to have some fun while watching whodunits.
I like the humor and the well written mysteries. I enjoy the interaction of the characters. Good series. Highly recommend it
again I like being able to watch the shows I like at my leisure and I always liked dick van dyke in any roll he played
One of my favorite shows. I had just seen most of them on tv, but I still enjoyed them. The picture is very good. Crisp and sharp. The sound is very good.

Same excellence as the other seasons---back when television was wholesome, and you didn't have to worry about the kids watching the program.  No unnecessary violence, degrading language, and gratuitous sex just to try to appeal to prurient interests of some viewers. "Where have you gone Joe DiMaggio...."

season 5 is packed with stars that we all know, because we watched their shows. SEASON 5 has only 1 thing wrong with it, and that is the last show of the season. IT has part 1, then part 2, then to be continued. which means WE have to buy season 6 to find out WHO is destroying the city, WHY are they doing this ? AND even the hospital gets bombed !!!!!  I WANT SEASON 6 to get closer to finishing the series AND to find out WHO & WHY. the show is called OBSESSION.

Diagnosis Murder season five part two goes to the dark side as Dr. Sloan (Dick Van Dyke) is sentenced to prisonin a two part pilot for Fred Dryer (Police Chief Masters).  This was a spinoff series that never happened.  This was also a season when gimmick casting was overused (the cast of both versions of M*A*S*H, Happy Days, and Laverne & Shirley, plus various other celebrities now has-beens).  They also dropped all pretense of being a mystery series so Dr. Sloan could rant and rail against HMOs, requiring no murders to be solved.  And, resorting to the fashion of the day, they ended the season with a two part cliffhanger that was ultimately dragged over four episodes, well into the next season.

At times, things got a bit more melodramatic and less fun.  Still, it remained entertainingexcept for those episodes when it wasnt.
Liked the show
Had to have the entire series as soon as it was available.  It was a long wait, but worth it!

We love Diagnosis Murder . It is one of our  favorite DVD's that we watch over and over again

Sad news for the deaf and the hard of hearing....this show do not have Closed Caption (CC) or subtitle for the deaf/hard of hearing (SDH). 504 article law-require to have CC or SDH on all tv shows/movies.
This series is very funny and does a great job of highlighting Dick van Dyke's talents.  I found the later shows not quite as good as the first two years.
I would have to rank the Diagnosis Murder: Season 5 a five out of five. All the episodes are very interesting as usual, would recommend this title to anyone interested in Mysteries!
